IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO DEVELOP SAFE, AFFORDABLE HOUSING FOR FAMILIES AND SENIORS, BASED IN OUR BELIEF THAT HAVING A HOME IS A SACRED HUMAN RIGHT.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE OVERSIGHT TO ARCHDIOCESAN-AFFILIATED HOUSING COMPANIES. ANYCH IS AFFILIATED WITH THE NEW YORK INSTITUTE OF HUMAN DEVELOPMENT, INC., WHICH AIDS IN THE CREATION, SURVIVAL, AND GROWTH OF COMMUNITY-BASED ORGANIZATIONS THROUGH A BROAD RANGE OF TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE, CONSULTING SERVICES AND FINANCIAL SUPPORT. ANYCH IS ALSO AFFILIATED WITH THE CATHOLIC CHARITIES OF THE ARCHDIOCESE OF NEW YORK AND OTHER ARCHDIOCESAN ENTITIES.
IRS990.Desc: AFFORDABLE HOUSING PROJECT OVERSIGHT:THE ASSOCIATION OF NEW YORK CATHOLIC HOMES OPERATES UNDER THE AUSPICES OF THE ARCHDIOCESE OF NEW YORK TO PROTECT AND PRESERVE MORE THAN 3,000 HOUSING UNITS OWNED BY 42 ARCHDIOCESAN-SPONSORED HOUSING CORPORATIONS. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO WORKS TO BUILD NEW AFFORDABLE HOUSING UNITS ON DESIGNATED ARCHDIOCESAN AND HOUSING-CORPORATION-OWNED PROPERTIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANYCH HAS A BUSINESS SERVICES AGREEMENT WITH CATHOLIC CHARITIES COMMUNITY SERVICES UNDER WHICH CCCS PROVIDES FISCAL OPERATIONS SERVICES FOR WHICH IT CHARGED ANYCH $77,667 IN THE YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS A MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION WITH A SOLE MEMBER, CATHOLIC CHARITIES ALLIANCE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SOLE MEMBER OF THE ORGANIZATION ELECTS OR REMOVES DIRECTORS OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FOLLOWING GOVERNANCE DECISIONS ARE RESERVED TO THE MEMBER: 1) REMOVAL OF ANY DIRECTOR WITHOUT CAUSE 2) ANY AMENDMENT TO THE CERTIFICATE OF INCORPORATION, BY-LAWS OR MISSION STATEMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION 3) APPROVAL OF A PLAN OF MERGER OR CONSOLIDATION OF THE CORPORATION, OR DISSOLUTION OF THE CORPORATION 4) APPROVAL OF THE SALE, MORTGAGE, LEASE, EXCHANGE OR OTHER DISPOSITION OF ALL OR SUBSTANTIALLY ALL OF THE ASSETS OF THE CORPORATION 5) DETERMINATION OF THE NUMBER OF DIRECTORS OF THE GOVERNING BODY

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS DISTRIBUTED TO MEMBERS OF THE BOARD'S EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE AND THEN THE BOARD FOR REVIEW AND DISCUSSION AT THEIR RESPECTIVE MEETINGS PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY WHICH COVERS ALL DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, COMMITTEE MEMBERS ("INTERESTED PERSONS"). INTERESTED PERSONS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST TO THE BOARD PRIOR TO ANY ACTION ON SUCH CONTRACT OR TRANSACTION. IF A POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST WERE TO ARISE, THE INTERESTED PERSON MAY NOT VOTE ON THE RELATED TRANSACTION. ALL DISCUSSION AND DELIBERATION IS DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MINUTES. THE BOARD IS RESPONSIBLE TO ENSURE THAT THE STATED PROCESS OCCURS IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE POLICY. ALL BOARD MEMBERS MUST ANNUALLY SIGN A STATEMENT AND DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
STANLEY GRAYSON WAS COMPENSATED FOR HOUSING AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT CONSULTING SERVICES AND NOT FOR SERVING IN HIS CAPACITY AS A BOARD MEMBER.

THE ORGANIZATION HAS A COMMITTEE THAT ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT OF ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT. THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
